always so toxic.

267
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:27,629
He…

268
00:17:28,672 --> 00:17:30,758
wanted me to believe that,

269
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:32,134
I was nothing.

270
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:34,845
Nothing without his approval.

271
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:37,765
And…

272
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:43,270
That led me to ignore all of
Anton's red flags when we were starting.

273
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:45,856
Until…

274
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:47,691
Nothing.

275
00:17:50,027 --> 00:17:52,196
I couldn't get out. [sobs]

276
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:57,910
[melancholic music continues]

277
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,329
[sniffles] And Lucas…

278
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:02,372
[Mel sniffles]

279
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:07,961
Lucas will always be that one light,

280
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:10,756
during the darkest time of my life.

281
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:13,509
[Mel sniffles]

282
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:16,637
He became my support.

283
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:19,932
A temporary pain killer.

284
00:18:24,019 --> 00:18:25,896
He made everything bearable.

285
00:18:25,979 --> 00:18:29,650
[melancholic music continues]

286
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:30,859
And…

287
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:33,779
Yeah, we had our shot.

288
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:35,280
But…

289
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:37,741
It just didn't work. [scoffs]

290
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:40,786
It's over.

291
00:18:47,376 --> 00:18:49,294
As for what you had together, Erica.

292
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:52,673
Yours was cut short.

293
00:18:54,174 --> 00:18:55,384
So…

294
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:59,054
If you think this is the right time

295
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:00,430
for the both of you,

296
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:04,017
I'll be fine with it.

297
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:09,231
[melancholic music continues]

298
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:11,900
From now on,

299
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:15,362
I'm going to stick to the plan.

300
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:19,241
To not break.

301
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:23,704
And…

302
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:28,125
- I can only do it if I do some intense…
- [music becomes hopeful]

303
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:29,960
Self-care

304
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:31,920
and self-love.

305
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,714
[hopeful music continues]

306
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:35,132
To hell with men, right?

307
00:19:35,215 --> 00:19:36,925
[both chuckling]

308
00:19:38,302 --> 00:19:40,846
I'll pull an
Attorney Erica Melendez attitude.

309
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:42,264
[chuckling]

310
00:19:42,347 --> 00:19:43,807
I don't know if that's a compliment

311
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:45,934
- [laughing]
- or an insult.

312
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:48,353
- It's a compliment!
- [Erica laughs]

313
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:52,107
You're the patron
saint of strong, independent,

314
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:54,902
and emotionally unavailable women.

315
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:59,156
[both laughing]

316
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:02,701
[music fades]

317
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:03,827
[Marco] Erica.

318
00:20:06,496 --> 00:20:08,624
[tense music playing]

319
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,542
[monitor beeping]

320
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:12,002
[Marco] <i>Kyo flatlined.</i>

321
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:17,257
[tense music continues]

322
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:25,140
Oslo is singing like a canary.

323
00:20:28,518 --> 00:20:29,686
[file thuds]

324
00:20:30,687 --> 00:20:33,065
The digital forensic report just came in.

325
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:35,901
The videos on the USB?

326
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:39,238
Verified. Authentic.

327
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:41,573
No tampering, no edits.

328
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:43,992
- It's crystal clear that you were present
- [music fades]

329
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:46,745
when they were killed
and thrown into the river.

330
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:48,830
As we speak,

331
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:52,542
the complaint affidavit
to be submitted to the DOJ.

332
00:20:53,001 --> 00:20:54,169
In a few days,

333
00:20:54,836 --> 00:20:56,713
your arrest is imminent.

334
00:20:57,381 --> 00:20:59,216
And you'll end up here.

335
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:02,886
You'll only get
bombarded with the same questions

336
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:04,680
so if I were you,

337
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:06,181
as early as now,

338
00:21:07,057 --> 00:21:08,308
I'd start talking.

339
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:11,520
[investigator breathes deeply]

340
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:14,481
Tell me in detail
what happened to all of them.

341
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:18,652
Were they all dumped into the lake?

342
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:24,741
- [Oslo breathes heavily]
- [suspenseful music playing]

343
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:25,826
[Oslo] If I…

344
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:27,744
Tell you everything,

345
00:21:29,204 --> 00:21:30,706
will you grant me immunity?

346
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,835
You'll put me in witness protection?

347
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:38,922
Whatever you think
you know about Laurence Kyo,

348
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:40,966
I'm sure that… [exhales deeply]

349
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,093
It's only this much.

350
00:21:45,345 --> 00:21:46,555
He may be dead…

351
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:49,516
But the organization he handles?

352
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:53,312
It's too massive to dissolve.

353
00:21:55,355 --> 00:21:57,858
I'm certain someone else
has already taken up his position.

354
00:21:59,234 --> 00:22:00,527
And I'm also certain that,

355
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:02,237
it was him who ordered,

356
00:22:03,238 --> 00:22:04,573
to have me killed.

357
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:08,076
Sir, I beg you.

358
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,619
I need protection!

359
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:13,665
I will give you all of the information
of the entire organization.

360
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,959
Even their connections
outside the Philippines.

361
00:22:16,668 --> 00:22:17,878
Okay, okay.

362
00:22:17,961 --> 00:22:20,672
We will put you
under our protective custody.

363
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:22,007
But…

364
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,761
That's if you give us good information.

365
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:28,764
Then we'll talk about your immunity.

366
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:32,559
Lost beauty queens.

367
00:22:32,642 --> 00:22:36,897
[dramatic music playing]

368
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:46,406
[music turns suspenseful]

369
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:47,532
<i>- Don't!</i>
<i>- Move!</i>

370
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:49,534
<i>- No!</i>
- [gun cocks]

371
00:22:49,618 --> 00:22:50,535
[gunshot]

372
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:52,079
[Oslo] Herlene Guinto.

373
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:54,706
Shot in the head. Tossed in the lake.

374
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:57,709
Janina Locsin.

375
00:22:58,585 --> 00:23:00,337
Also shot in the head.

376
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:02,380
Lake.

377
00:23:04,758 --> 00:23:06,218
<i>As for LJ,</i>

378
00:23:07,844 --> 00:23:09,262
<i>she was stabbed front and back.</i>

379
00:23:09,971 --> 00:23:11,139
<i>Also in the lake.</i>

380
00:23:12,849 --> 00:23:16,937
- [shovel thudding]
- [dirt shuffling]

381
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:21,483
[suspenseful music intensifies]

382
00:23:42,629 --> 00:23:46,800
[music becomes ominous, fades]

383
00:23:46,883 --> 00:23:48,593
[birds chirping]

384
00:23:59,396 --> 00:24:05,652
[foreboding music playing]

385
00:24:08,947 --> 00:24:11,741
[dramatic music sting]

386
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:15,579
<i>Do you ever feel like</i>
<i>you're living on borrowed time?</i>

387
00:24:15,662 --> 00:24:18,248
<i>That you've got what you have,</i>
<i>at the cost of others.</i>

388
00:24:18,331 --> 00:24:20,584
<i>That at any time,</i>
<i>it could all just fall apart.</i>

389
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:22,669
[screaming]

390
00:24:22,752 --> 00:24:24,087
<i>Help… </i>[crying]

391
00:24:25,922 --> 00:24:28,133
<i>What happened?</i>
<i>Is it true that they found a body?</i>

392
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:30,510
[Edong] <i>Did you all think you got past me?</i>

393
00:24:33,138 --> 00:24:35,015
<i>He did this on</i>
<i>purpose to rub it in our face</i>

394
00:24:35,098 --> 00:24:38,602
<i>that he won't let our dream</i>
<i>of growing old together come true!</i>
